Contributions Subject to Special Rules
Special rules apply if you contribute: • Clothing or household items;
• A car, boat, or airplane;
• Taxidermy property;
• Property subject to a debt;
• A partial interest in property;
• A fractional interest in tangible personal property;
• A qualified conservation contribution;
• A future interest in tangible personal property;
• Inventory from your business; or
• A patent or other intellectual property. These special rules are described next. Clothing and Household Items You can’t take a deduction for clothing or household items 
you donate unless the clothing or household items are in 
good used condition or better. Exception. You can take a deduction for a contribution of 
